{
  "texts": [
    "The model would provide alternatives that deviated from the source text and introduced misleading and incorrect information.",
    "These erroneous alternatives were sometimes not (directly) related to gender (Example 11) but often the (feminine) terms were inaccurately replaced with masculine alternatives.",
    "These translations not only distort the intended message and thus the accuracy of the translation but also often perpetuate gender biases that are deeply ingrained in our society.",
    "Erroneous and biased translations that misrepresent the source content furthermore carry the risk of alienating or excluding individuals who do not conform to traditional gender norms.",
    "Overall, these findings underscore the need for continued research and development to enhance our understanding of LLMs' handling of genderrelated nuances in translation."
  ]
}